sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K809329
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: BioBricks of Toc75_SPtom40 (K809326) is linked with GAL promoter and ADH1 terminator. When expressed in cytoplasm, The Toc75 will be directed on mitochondrial outer membrane as a channel protein
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Luohao Xu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: All parts should be linked correctly without nonsense mutation and frameshift mutation

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Toc75_SPto
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Toc75 is linked with signal peptide of Tom40, thus can be directed on mitochondrial outer membrane as a beta-barrel protein
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Luohao Xu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Both parts should be linked correctly without nonsense mutation and frameshift mutation

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K809601
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: GAL promoter (kozak) without start codon ATG
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is based on BBa_J63006 and is without ATG start codon. It is more convenient to use.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jianhui Gong

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: SPtom40
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the signal peptied of Tom40, which can direct the assembly of β-barrel protein into outer membrane of mitochondrion
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Luohao Xu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Eukaryote-wide sequence analysis of mitochondrial β-barrel outer membrane proteins
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: No modification for the original sequence

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Toc75
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Toc75 is the outer membrane translocation channel in chloroplast, which belongs to the transmembrane β-barrel protein family.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Luohao Xu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It is cloned by reversal transcription of Toc75 mRNA extracted from the cells of Cyanidioschyzon merolae

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: SPtom40
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the signal peptied of Tom40, which can direct the assembly of β-barrel protein into outer membrane of mitochondrion
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Luohao Xu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Eukaryote-wide sequence analysis of mitochondrial β-barrel outer membrane proteins
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: No modification for the original sequence

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Toc75
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Toc75 is the outer membrane translocation channel in chloroplast, which belongs to the transmembrane β-barrel protein family.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Luohao Xu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It is cloned by reversal transcription of Toc75 mRNA extracted from the cells of Cyanidioschyzon merolae
